Key Match Events: Aaron Nola allowed five runs (four earned) on nine hits (two homers) and two walks while striking out five in 4 2/3 innings.
Pre-Game Insights: Aaron Nola entered his 29th start of the season on a hot streak, posting a 1.44 ERA with 24 strikeouts and just six walks in his previous four games.
Post-Match Reflections: Aaron Nola said he was 'a little out of sync' and threw away too many pitches, while catcher Garrett Stubbs helped Nola navigate the Marlins' lineup and bailed him out offensively.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Garrett Stubbs took advantage of Miami's inexperienced defense, bunting in his first two plate appearances and reaching base both times.
Others: Aaron Nola was working with a tweaked arsenal, leaning on his four-seam fastball and his knuckle curve more than usual, and catcher Garrett Stubbs caught a popup in foul territory to end a troublesome fifth inning.
